extends ../_layout/_docs.pug

block variables
  - var slug = 'elements'
  - var parent = 'base'

block docs
  h1 Elements

  p The #[code elements] folder add some styles for basic HTML elements.

  pre.code(data-lang='SCSS')
    code
      :highlight(lang="scss")
        // ELEMENTS
        @forward "~glsass/src/elements/elements.headings";
        @forward "~glsass/src/elements/elements.images";
        @forward "~glsass/src/elements/elements.lists";
        @forward "~glsass/src/elements/elements.links";
        @forward "~glsass/src/elements/elements.page";
        @forward "~glsass/src/elements/elements.tables";

        /* Or import all of elements */

        // ELEMENTS
        @forward "~glsass/src/elements";

  p You can notice that the order of file is alphabetic, even if "top" tags like #[code html]
    |  and #[code body] are inside the #[code _elements.page.scss] file, because each file
    |  includes its own elements.

  h2 Headings - #[em _elements.headings.scss]

  p All #[codd hn] (h1 to h6) styles are generated from the global settings.
    |  This is why there is there is not configurable variables (and to maitain
    |  some consistency with the utilities classes: #[code .u-hn]).
    br
    | About the #[code line-height] property, it's automatically calculated
    |  to respect the vertical rhythm for headings.

  .p-example
    h1 Heading 1
    h2 Heading 2
    h3 Heading 3
    h4 Heading 4
    h5 Heading 5
    h6 Heading 6
  pre.code(data-lang='HTML')
    code
      :highlight(lang="html")
        <h1>Heading 1</h1>
        <h2>Heading 2</h2>
        <h3>Heading 3</h3>
        <h4>Heading 4</h4>
        <h5>Heading 5</h5>
        <h6>Heading 6</h6>

  h2 Images - #[em _elements.images.scss]

  p It adds some default rules for alternative text or to remove the space that can appear unnder
    |  the element.
    br
    | Images also have a #[code max-width] set to 100% to facilitate fluid responsive needs.
    |  By default, even if images are generated with #[code width] and #[code height] attributes,
    |  they still be fluid. This behavior can be changed by setting the variables #[code $e-images-static-size]
    |  at #[code true].

  pre.code(data-lang='SCSS')
    code
      :highlight(lang="scss")
        @forward "~glsass/src/elements/elements.images" with (
          $e-images-static-size: true,
        );

  h2 Lists - #[em _elements.lists.scss]

  p Lists are lightly modify to bring some space on the left and bottom.
    br
    | Since there is differents kind of list, we could have moved this rules in the #[code _generic.shared.scss] file.
    |  But since there are some specificities between all of them, it's simpler to regroup it inside a unique place.

  .p-example
      ul
        li Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
        li Consectetur adipiscing elit
        li Sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt
          ul
            li Ut labore et dolore magna aliqua
            li Ut enim ad minim veniam
        li Quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris
        li Nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat

      ol
        li Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
        li Consectetur adipiscing elit
        li Sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt

      dl
        dt The ingredients:
        dd
          ul
            li 100 g. flour
            li 10 g. sugar
            li 1 cup water
            li 2 eggs
            li salt, pepper
        dt The procedure:
        dd
          ol
            li Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
            li Pour in wet ingredients.
            li Mix for 10 minutes.
            li Bake for one hour at 300 degrees.
        dt Notes:
        dd The recipe may be improved by adding raisins.
  pre.code(data-lang='HTML')
    code
      :highlight(lang="html")
        <ul>
          <li>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet</li>
          <li>Consectetur adipiscing elit</li>
          <li>Sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt
            <ul>
              <li>Ut labore et dolore magna aliqua</li>
              <li>Ut enim ad minim veniam</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris</li>
          <li>Nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat</li>
        </ul>

        <ol>
          <li>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet</li>
          <li>Consectetur adipiscing elit</li>
          <li>Sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt</li>
        </ol>

        <dl>
          <dt>The ingredients:</dt>
          <dd>
            <ul>
              <li>100 g. flour</li>
              <li>10 g. sugar</li>
              <li>1 cup water</li>
              <li>2 eggs</li>
              <li>salt, pepper</li>
            </ul>
          </dd>
          <dt>The procedure:</dt>
          <dd>
            <ol>
              <li>Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.</li>
              <li>Pour in wet ingredients.</li>
              <li>Mix for 10 minutes.</li>
              <li>Bake for one hour at 300 degrees.</li>
            </ol>
          </dd>
          <dt>Notes:</dt>
          <dd>The recipe may be improved by adding raisins.</dd>
        </dl>

  h2 Links - #[em _elements.links.scss]

  p We set the default color for link to preserve the current color of the text and add underlines.

  .p-example
    a(href="/") Link to the home
  pre.code(data-lang='HTML')
    code
      :highlight(lang="html")
        <a href="/">Link to the home</a>

  p By default, all external link (with a #[code target="_blank"]), will have append an arrow indicator (#[code â†—] or #[code #{'&nearr;'}] HTML entity).
    br
    |  This settings can be modified by setting the option #[code $e-links-external-indicator] at #[code false].

  .p-example
    a(href="https://developer.mozilla.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer") Link to MDN homepage
  pre.code(data-lang='HTML')
    code
      :highlight(lang="html")
        <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Link to MDN homepage</a>

  h2 Page - #[em _elements.page.scss]

  p This file contains main declarations for #[code html] and #[code body] tags. It's used to
    |  set default #[code font-size], #[code line-height] or #[code color] and improvement for iOS.

  h2 Tables - #[em _elements.tables.scss]

  p We add an unique rule to ensure tables fill up as much space as possible.
